Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Billericay 
    and Stock. See also Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Chelmsford. 
    See also Table 2, note (o).

Created 24.3.1888 out of the parishes of Chignall Smealey and 
    Chignall St. James. See also Table 2, note (o).
Abolished 24.3.1888 and added to the parish of Chignall.

Abolished 24.3.1888 and divided between the parishes of Writtle, 
    Broomfield and Chignall.

Abolished 24.3.1889 and added to the parish of Ingatestone 
    & Fryerning.

Created 1.4.1987 out of the parish of Great Baddow. See also 
    Table 2, note (o).
Created 1.4.1949 from the parishes of Little Leighs, Great Leighs and Little Waltham. See also Table 2, note (o).

Abolished 1.4.1949 and divided between the parishes of Great & 
    Little Leighs and Little Waltham.

Created 1.4.1987 out of the Maldon unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (o).

Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of High Roothing. See also 
    Table 2, notes (i) and (m).

Created 1.4.1954 out of the parish of Writtle. See also Table 
    2, note (o).

Abolished 24.3.1889 and added to the parish of Ingatestone 
    & Fryerning.

    See also Table 2, note (k).

Abolished 1.4.1949 and added to the parish of Great & Little 
    Leighs.

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (j) and (l).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Maldon.

    (n).

Created 1.4.1987 out of the Maldon unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (o).

Created 1.4.1987 out of the parish of Woodham Ferrers. See 
    also Table 2, note (o).

Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of White Roothing. See also 
    Table 2, notes (i) and (oq.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Chelmsford 
    and Writtle.

Abolished 1.4.1987 and divided between the parishes of South 
    Woodham Ferrers and Woodham Ferrers & Bicknacre. See also Table 2, note 
    (h).

Created 1.4.1987 out of the parishes of Danbury and Woodham 
    Ferrers. See also Table 2, note (o).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed part of the parish of Buttsbury. See
